60.8	Aliyah	Aliyah	Aliyah . It is a basic tenet of Zionist ideology. The opposite action, emigration from Israel, is referred to as yerida ("descent"). The return to the Holy Land has been a Jewish aspiration since the Babylonian exile. Large scale immigration to Eretz Israel and later Israel began in 1882.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/86/Israel-flag01c.jpg/150px-Israel-flag01c.jpg
